I’ve identified a concrete gap to fix: ambiguity generation currently relies on cue-ranking when cues exist, so adaptive-logit disagreement can be dropped. I’m making a narrow compiler change to also emit explicit adaptive pair ambiguities when logits disagree with cue top-family, and I’ll add tests for `frame->epistemic` coverage plus the disagreement path.
apply patch
